{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TKzCLm2oPYpkFnM5YYPMd7","type":"tool_result","content":"  1755→---\n  1756→\n  1757→## Task 17: LLM Client Implementation\n  1758→\n  1759→**Files:**\n  1760→- Create: `internal/evolution/llmclient.go`\n  1761→- Create: `internal/evolution/llmclient_test.go`\n  1762→\n  1763→The evolution system needs to invoke an LLM. Reuse the same pattern as the prompt\n  1764→adapter — shell out to a command (e.g., `claude -p`).\n  1765→\n  1766→**Step 1: Write failing test**\n  1767→\n  1768→```go\n  1769→func TestCommandLLMClientPrintMode(t *testing.T) {\n  1770→\tscript := filepath.Join(t.TempDir(), \"fake-claude.sh\")\n  1771→\tos.WriteFile(script, []byte(\"#!/bin/sh\\necho \\\"ARGS:$*\\\"\\necho \\\"STDIN:$(cat)\\\"\\n\"), 0755)\n  1772→\n  1773→\tc := &CommandLLMClient{Command: script, Args: []string{}}\n  1774→\tresult, err := c.Complete(context.Background(), \"You are a helpful assistant.\", \"Summarize this text\")\n  1775→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n  1776→\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"-p\")\n  1777→\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"--system-prompt\")\n  1778→\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"--output-format text\")\n  1779→\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"STDIN:Summarize this text\")\n  1780→}\n  1781→```\n  1782→\n  1783→**Step 2: Run test, implement, run test again**\n  1784→\n  1785→The `CommandLLMClient` invokes the LLM command in print mode (`-p`) for\n  1786→non-interactive output. The system prompt is passed via the `--system-prompt`\n  1787→flag so the LLM can distinguish it from user content, and `--output-format text`\n  1788→is used to avoid JSON wrappers. Only the user prompt is piped via stdin.\n  1789→\n  1790→**Step 3: Commit**\n  1791→\n  1792→```bash\n  1793→git add internal/evolution/\n  1794→git commit -m \"feat(evolution): add CommandLLMClient for LLM invocation\"\n  1795→```\n  1796→\n  1797→---\n  1798→\n  1799→## Task 18: Daemon Integration — Trigger and Debounce\n  1800→\n  1801→**Files:**\n  1802→- Modify: `internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n  1803→- Modify: `cmd/cloched/main.go`\n  1804→- Create: `internal/evolution/trigger.go`"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb4351ca-c901-4b1b-a8ba-6cfbda6fb109","uuid":"ee6639aa-f472-4417-99eb-cb1422cbac5b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md","content":"---\n\n## Task 17: LLM Client Implementation\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/evolution/llmclient.go`\n- Create: `internal/evolution/llmclient_test.go`\n\nThe evolution system needs to invoke an LLM. Reuse the same pattern as the prompt\nadapter — shell out to a command (e.g., `claude -p`).\n\n**Step 1: Write failing test**\n\n```go\nfunc TestCommandLLMClientPrintMode(t *testing.T) {\n\tscript := filepath.Join(t.TempDir(), \"fake-claude.sh\")\n\tos.WriteFile(script, []byte(\"#!/bin/sh\\necho \\\"ARGS:$*\\\"\\necho \\\"STDIN:$(cat)\\\"\\n\"), 0755)\n\n\tc := &CommandLLMClient{Command: script, Args: []string{}}\n\tresult, err := c.Complete(context.Background(), \"You are a helpful assistant.\", \"Summarize this text\")\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"-p\")\n\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"--system-prompt\")\n\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"--output-format text\")\n\tassert.Contains(t, result, \"STDIN:Summarize this text\")\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test, implement, run test again**\n\nThe `CommandLLMClient` invokes the LLM command in print mode (`-p`) for\nnon-interactive output. The system prompt is passed via the `--system-prompt`\nflag so the LLM can distinguish it from user content, and `--output-format text`\nis used to avoid JSON wrappers. Only the user prompt is piped via stdin.\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/evolution/\ngit commit -m \"feat(evolution): add CommandLLMClient for LLM invocation\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 18: Daemon Integration — Trigger and Debounce\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n- Modify: `cmd/cloched/main.go`\n- Create: `internal/evolution/trigger.go`","numLines":50,"startLine":1755,"totalLines":2053}}}
